<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-631-299  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 631 299.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The LocalNetter  August 1990 v10 n8 p15(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Architecture Technology Corp. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Jupiter Technology software links TCP/IP to System/370. (JupiterTechnology's 9770 TCPaccess and 9770 NFSaccess computer networksoftware)(IBM System/370) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Jupiter Technology Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   9770 TCPaccess (Computer network software) (Product introduction)9770 NFSaccess (Computer network software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Transmission Control Protocol-Internet Protocol (Computer NetworkProtocol)Product IntroductionNetwork SoftwareApplications Programming Interface.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Jupiter Technology, Inc., has added two software packages that enable TCP/IPnetwork users to access System/370 mainframe files and applications withoutlearning different operating system commands.andP;  The new software offerings arecalled 9770 TCPaccess and 9770 NFSaccess and are used together with Jupiter'schannel- attached 9770 Network Protocol Server to let the mainframe act as anetwork file server.andP;  Network users see one file system which now includesboth local and mainframe files.andM;The 9770 TCPaccess software provides application programmatic interfaces(APIs) to the TCP/IP network.andP;  It allows interprogram communicationsincluding NFS (Network File System) file server support, domain name service,and Berkeley Socket interfaces.andM;Used with the 9770 Network Protocol Server, 9770 TCPaccess software supportsup to six simultaneous TCP/IP network links to the mainframe.andM;With 9770 NFSaccess software, the NFS application for file sharing isextended from the network to System/370 MVS mainframes.andP;  It supports standardMVS security packages, data back-up, and archive procedures.andP;  Network usersin an open access computing environment can use the mainframe withoutjeopardizing mainframe security, while increasing network data reliabilityand security.andM;Available immediately, prices for the 9700 TCPaccess Software start at$33,500; prices for the 9770 NFSaccess Mainframe Application Software startat $11,150, with availability within 90 days.andM;Information:  Jupiter Technology, INC., 2402 W. Beardsley Road, Phoenix, AZ85027; (800) 525-4790.andO;</TEXT></DOC>